<component name="TendAnscale" category="Tend">  <overview>
    <authors>
      <author>Martin Cole</author>
    </authors>
    <summary>Scale the anisotropic component of the tensors. This maintains
the isotropic component of the tensor, and fixes either the trace or
determinant, while scaling up (or down) the deviatoric component of the
tensor. Good for exaggerating the shape of nearly isotropic tensors.</summary>
    <description>
      <p>Scale the anisotropic component of the tensors. This maintains
the isotropic component of the tensor, and fixes either the trace or
determinant, while scaling up (or down) the deviatoric component of the
tensor. Good for exaggerating the shape of nearly isotropic tensors.</p>
      <p>Scale: Amount by which to scale deviatoric component of tensor. This value should be a float.</p>
    </description>
    <examplesr></examplesr>
  </overview>
  <io>
    <inputs lastportdynamic="no">
      <port>
        <name>nin</name>
	<datatype>SCIRun::Nrrd</datatype>
      </port>
    </inputs>
    <outputs>
      <port>
        <name>nout</name>
	<datatype>SCIRun::Nrrd</datatype>
      </port>
    </outputs>
  </io>
  <testing>
  </testing>
</component>
